A woman in her 70s has died following a crash in Colwyn Bay. Police were called to a one-vehicle collision involving a Peugeot Partner van on Conway Road in the West End area at around 13:00 BST on 3 July. A female passenger, who was airlifted to Ysbyty Glan Clwyd with serious injuries, died on 4 July.A male driver, also in his 70s, was taken to Ysbyty Glan Clwyd by ambulance, where he remains in a stable condition.
